{"key":"processedPost-9895833","value":{"id":9895833,"first":9895757,"last":9898919,"when":1236017060,"utime":"03/02/09 08:04 PM","cleanedPost":"It's a bad idea to pipe coolmists into a tub.&nbsp; It will saturate the substrate, resulting in poor performance.&nbsp; With a tub and cased substrates, no humidification is necessary.&nbsp; Don't use polyfill in the holes.&nbsp; Leave them open for fresh air, and mist as necessary to replace the moisture that evaporates from your substrate or casing layer.&nbsp; <br />The best use for your humidifiers is to run them as they came out of the box, in the room you grow in to raise the ambient humidity a bit.<br />RR"}}